        <num>CC 1740</num>
        <heading>1740.  Division following substitution of common descendants</heading>
        <content>
          <p>Art. 1740.  Division following substitution of common descendants
If the common descendants of the spouses find themselves substituted to both or one of the spouses, the property to which the common descendants are entitled shall be divided among them in accordance with the provisions of Chapter 2 of Title I of Book III.</p>
        </content>
